28/06/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A ten-day joint military drill including members of the Croatian armed forces and the US National Guard from Minnesota wrapped up at the Gasinci training base in Croatia on Tuesday (27 June).
The exercise was aimed at strengthening the Croatian Army's capacities to participate in international peacekeeping missions, in line with NATO standards.
Also Tuesday, Foreign Minister Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic reiterated her expectations that a clear signal for Croatia's bid to join NATO would be given during the Alliance's November summit in Riga.
Grabar-Kitarovic made the comments at parliament, while responding to deputies' questions.
(Vjesnik - 28/06/06;
HINA - 27/06/06)
